'''Argives''' ([[Greek language|Greek]] ''{{polytonic|Ἀργεῖοι}}'', ''Argeioi''; Latin ''Argivi'') means literally the inhabitants of '''[[Argos]]'''. In the [[Homer]]ic ''[[Iliad]]'' and ''[[Odyssey]]'', and in later classical epics, "Argives" is an alternate name for the '''[[Achaeans]]''' or [[Greeks]] in general.

